    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Drake Baldwin** (70.94) and **Kyle Tucker** (70.88) headline the Austin Waves lineup as our elite plays. **Drake Baldwin** earns his spot through a favorable park factor and a solid hitting environment, while **Kyle Tucker** remains our cornerstone, buoyed by a strong 10% SP skill advantage against May. **Sam Antonacci** (64.32) also emerges as a high-value start; his placement in the leadoff spot combined with a favorable matchup against Canning makes him a core contributor today. While **Jackson Merrill** (60.31) sees a significant hit due to a platoon disadvantage against Kay, the 5.66 xERA of the opposing starter keeps his ceiling high enough to merit a start in our OF5 slot.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Coby Mayo** (50.85). He narrowly missed the cut behind **Heliot Ramos** (50.58) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (51.19), though the optimizer ultimately favored the latter two due to their specific order advantages and recent form. We continue to monitor the status of **Jordan Westburg**, who remains on the IL, and while we considered **Marcell Ozuna** (40.49) for his raw power, his low efficiency score against a tough arm like Burns keeps him firmly on the pine to preserve our game caps. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of the matchups for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.78) and **Jacob Wilson** (56.25). Both players face SPs with low xERAs, and while their platoon dynamic is neutral or slightly favorable, their reliance on contact against quality arms introduces a floor risk. We are also wary of **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages** facing elite hold SPs, as their stolen base potential is marginally suppressed by defensive efficiency. With these factors in mind, the Austin Waves are positioned for high-variance production, provided our leadoff hitters like **Sam Antonacci** and **Jacob Wilson** can set the table effectively against their respective left-handed matchups.",
